PRACTICAL 2: Working with vCenter Server Appliance
Prerequisites

• Practical 1 completed
• ESXi host installed and running
• Network connectivity between ESXi and host system

Steps

Run the vCenter Server Appliance (VCSA) installer from the installer directory.

Select Deploy vCenter Server Appliance and accept the license agreement.

Enter ESXi host IP address, root username, and password.

Provide a name and password for the vCenter appliance.

Select deployment size and enable thin disk provisioning.

Configure network settings using DHCP.

Complete Stage 1 installation and wait for deployment to finish.

Continue to Stage 2 configuration via browser.

Configure SSO domain name, credentials, and time synchronization.

Log in to vCenter using the provided IP address.

Create a Datacenter and Cluster.

Add ESXi host to the cluster using root credentials.

Assign evaluation or license key through Licensing section.

Configure NTP settings for time synchronization.
